    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Abbott</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 145.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 164, of the 17th ultimo,
                    in regard to the interpretation of section 10 of article <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >iii</hi> of the consular convention of 1850 between the United States and
                    Colombia, relating to the administration of the estates of deceased persons by
                    consular officers.</p>
                <p>I approve the tenor of your note on the subject to Señor Roldán.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
